{
  "buggy_files": ["sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["azx_resume", "azx_init_chip"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "After suspend to RAM, the driver's error-handling state variables (chip->single_cmd, chip->polling_mode, chip->poll_count) are not reset. When azx_get_response encounters timeouts during resume, it sets chip->single_cmd=1 and calls azx_free_cmd_io. However, in azx_init_chip, the command I/O is only reinitialized if chip->single_cmd==0 (line 1222-1223: 'if (!chip->single_cmd) azx_init_cmd_io(chip)'). Since these error-handling flags persist across suspend/resume cycles without being reset, the CORB/RIRB (Command Output/Response Input Ring Buffers) remain uninitialized, causing the codec to become unresponsive. The fix requires resetting chip->single_cmd, chip->polling_mode, and chip->poll_count to their initial values in azx_resume or azx_init_chip during the resume path."
}

